                                                         X Application Panel
                                                        X Window Filemanager
                                                             X Privacy Guard
                                                                            
   Version 0.9.7 - © Rasca, Berlin 1999 - 2000, published under the
   [1]GNU GPL
   Warning: This is a beta release, don't use it to copy or move critical
   data!
   
     * Needed libraries: [2]glib/gtk+ 1.2.0 or newer! Note: You can check
       this with the command 'gtk-config --version', don't use version
       1.2.4, seems to be problematic with xap.
     * Download: Get the current [3]source code of xap and xwf via HTTP
       or first checkout the [4]ChangeLog to see what has changed since
       the last release. For a RPM package have a look at Romildo's ftp
       site [5]ftp://urano.iceb.ufop.br/pub/xap/
     * Installation: see the [6]INSTALL document ..
     * xap
       [7][screendump-xap] Usage: xap [-v] [-t] [-g <geom>]
       xap looks for a directory named '$HOME/.xap'. For every included
       subdirectoy a notebook page is created in the GUI. Every symbolic
       link in this subdirectories will result in an application button
       to start this application or to drop file names which will be
       passed as arguments while launching this program.
       A Drag and Drop of an application to the label of a notebook-page
       will create a new program button. Use mouse button 3 over a
       program-button to rename or delete a button.
     * xwf
       [8][screendump-xwf] Usage: xwf [-v] [directory] [-g <geom>]
       For a short description of the xwf application and a list of the
       keyboard short cuts look inside the included man-page.
     * xpg
       Usage: xpg [files ..]
     * Todo:
       Bug fixes..
       Code cleanups..
     * Links:
          + [9]Gtk+, X-Window GUI library
          + [10]Mlvwm, Mac-like window-manager
          + [11]Gnome, gtk+ based desktop environment
          + [12]XDND, Drag and Drop protocol
          + [13]XFCE, Desktop environment with modified xwf version
       
   |[14]Home|
   
   
